                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Ward, Angus I.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-23T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 23, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 23—7:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2074. Ward stated further accused were refused legal counsel, refused right
                    produce witnesses for defense, refused right question witnesses or plaintiffs or
                    other rebutting arguments. Re Contel 2064, November 23.</p>
                <p>Recommend no interpretive comment on trial and judgement at least until receipt
                    fuller information. Note personnel still without travel permits or schedule.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
